{"id":"project-LICHEN-xjhh","title":"bridge.rs: Unknown routing error codes silently treated as success","description":"File: rust/lichen-meshtastic/src/bridge.rs:78-98

The RoutingErrorCode::from(i32) implementation maps unknown values to RoutingErrorCode::None:

```rust
impl From<i32> for RoutingErrorCode {
    fn from(val: i32) -> Self {
        match val {
            0 => Self::None,
            ...
            35 => Self::PkiUnknownPubkey,
            _ => Self::None,  // BUG: Unknown codes treated as success
        }
    }
}
```

In process_incoming (line 227-235), this is used:
```rust
let error_code = RoutingErrorCode::from(e);
error: if error_code == RoutingErrorCode::None {
    None  // Treated as success!
} else {
    Some(error_code)
},
```

IMPACT: If Meshtastic firmware adds new error codes (e.g., code 36), LICHEN would treat them as successful routing, potentially leading to incorrect behavior.

FIX: Add an Unknown variant to RoutingErrorCode enum and handle it as an error condition in process_incoming.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T17:12:57.790543Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T17:12:57.790581Z"}

